{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05957/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05957"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:59:57"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman smokes a cigarette, sitting at her desk."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05957","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05957"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1/b10c2e2d-3dd2-4b31-8338-d99894b60fcf","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:04:49.862Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cyril, and Lesley Manville’s performance, offers a much different version of femininity or womanhood seen throughout the film. She is a far cry from the socialites that Reynolds dresses as well as the models and muses he treats as disposable aspects of his artistic practice. She does, of course, overlap somewhat with Alma in that she takes on a motherly role in caring for her distressed brother. But she adopts a tougher exterior, and viewers gain no insights into her personal or romantic lives. If Reynolds takes on certain traditionally feminine traits, then Cyril likewise adopts more masculine traits.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05957/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:744.5534690366972,77.91786123853213,564.0159116972479,608.6740252293579"}}}]}]}]}